                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p34m91x1v/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>7. Chronological position of the administration<lb/> of <persName>Samson</persName>\n                and <persName>Jephtah</persName> p. 234. 265 to 269., which<lb/> makes new the whole\n                period of Judges.</p>\n            <p>8. The <sic>highschool</sic> at <placeName>Ramah</placeName> 250-256.</p>\n            <p>9. Chronological investigation on <persName>David's</persName> seven<lb/> years in\n                    <placeName>Hebron</placeName>324</p>\n            <p>10. Reconciliation of <persName>I. Samuel</persName> 16.17. 18308</p>\n            <p>11. The wars of <persName>David</persName>337-344</p>\n            <p>12. The revolt under and after <persName>Solomon</persName>377-384</p>\n            <p>Almost the whole history of the Kings is new, having<lb/>\n                <sic>reconciliated</sic>\n                <persName>Samuel</persName>, Kings, and Chronicles, and<lb/> having compared\n                scriptural passages with the<lb/> late discoveries in <placeName>Nineveh</placeName>\n                xc.</p>\n            <p>The four appendices are totally new. I have established<lb/> that\n                    <persName>moses</persName> wrote the Pentateuch, that this law and<lb/> religion\n                was the code of the nation in all ages, which<lb/> was most emphatically negatived\n                by modern critics; that<lb/> the historical books were written much earlier than<lb/>\n                <persName>Jost</persName> and others believed; that art and science flourished<lb/>\n                among the ancient Israelites; and that they were thoroughly<lb/> democratic and\n                invincible patriots. In religion I have<lb/> not only rushed many a hypercritical\n                assertion; but<lb/> also the grand supposition, that the prophets did not<lb/>\n                understand Judaism until <persName>Jesus</persName> came to expound it.<lb/> The\n                faults you will find, and I am ready to hear<lb/> them.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Most Respectfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Isaac M. Wise</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Albany</placeName>\n                <date>December 7. 5614</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                <date>1854</date>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
